correctness.rationale: The extraction is largely incorrect and weakly traceable to the article, with at least one schema violation and many fabricated values. Key issues: (1) Schema violation: processParameters.plasmaPower is set to null, but the schema expects an object; this field should be omitted if not used. (2) Unsupported ALD details: aldSystem.aldMethod = TALD, reactantSelection.precursor entries (“In-Ga bimetallic precursor”, “diethyl zinc (DEZ)”) and coReactant = O3 for IGZO are not specified in the paper; carrierGas/purgingGas = N2 also not reported. (3) Fabricated process parameters: temperature (200 °C), pressure (0.1 mmHg), dosingTime, purgeTime, flowRates, nucleationPeriod, and saturation are not provided in the article. (4) Internal inconsistency in thickness control: growthPerCycle = 0.1 Å and numberofCycles = 100 imply ~1 nm, conflicting with filmThickness = 10 nm. (5) Supercycle design inconsistency: numberofSubcycles uses compound = “InGaZnO” (repeated three times) while subcycleSequence lists [In2O3, Ga2O3, ZnO]; the article only states In content was varied by cycle ratio without giving counts. (6) Material properties are largely invented and untraceable: refractive index, absorption coefficient, band gap, resistivity, carrier density, uniformity variation, conformality aspect ratio, atomic ratio (1.0:2.8:5.4), elemental concentration (10%), amorphous phase (not explicitly stated), film density, and mobility characterized by “Hall measurements” (the paper reports device μ_FE from transfer characteristics, not Hall). (7) onOffRatio = 1e6 is not reported. (8) Some items are correct: substrate (“8-in thermally oxidated p+ Si”), IGZO film thickness (10 nm), device structure (bottom-gate), and device-level metrics for device E (μ_FE = 16.9 cm^2/V·s, SS = 61.7 mV/dec, V_TH = 0.68 V). To correct: remove or justify unsupported reactants and ALD method, fix the plasmaPower null, align thickness control values with 10 nm, revise supercycleDesign to match article or omit counts, restrict device/material properties to those reported (and correct mobility method), and eliminate speculative parameters not in the source text.

completeness.rationale: The extraction is largely incorrect and not schema- or article-aligned. (1) Multiple processes are described in the article (devices A–F with different gate dielectrics, varying IGZO In ratios via ALD subcycle ratios, and different post-treatments; also AlOx grown by H2O vs O3), but only a single process is extracted, losing key variations. (2) Many values are fabricated and not traceable to the article: ALD temperature (200 °C), pressure (0.1 mmHg), dosing/purge times, flow rates, GPC (0.1 Å), number of cycles (100), precursors/co-reactant (DEZ, O3, “In–Ga bimetallic”), optical properties (n, band gap, absorption), electrical film properties (resistivity, carrier density), uniformity and conformality metrics, composition (XPS ratios), roughness, film density, on/off ratio, and safety/reproducibility statements. The article only specifies: substrate (8-in thermally oxidized p+ Si), IGZO thickness (10 nm), gate dielectrics and their thickness (7 nm), that IGZO is grown by ALD with In content controlled by ALD cycle ratio, device metrics (SS 61.7 mV/dec, μFE 16.9 cm2/Vs, VTH 0.68 V), vacuum during electrical measurement (<1e−5 torr), and post-anneal/treatments. (3) Schema violations/inconsistencies: plasmaPower is null (type mismatch), thicknessControl nests numberofCycles and filmThickness under growthPerCycle despite additionalProperties: false; filmThickness is duplicated; supercycleDesign.numberofSubcycles uses the compound “InGaZnO” repeatedly instead of per-oxide components, and counts are unsubstantiated; duplicate precursors listed for the same compound; numerous unverified units/values (e.g., film density unit and magnitude). (4) Supercycle design is not properly captured: the article states composition is controlled by In:Ga:Zn subcycle ratio (a:b:c), but no grounded counts/ratios are provided. To improve: extract multiple processes reflecting devices A–F or at least distinct IGZO ALD processes for different In ratios; include only article-supported values (substrate, 10-nm IGZO, gate dielectric types/thickness, device metrics); correct thicknessControl structure; remove null plasmaPower; avoid unreported precursors/co-reactants/parameters; and, if unknown, omit optional fields rather than fabricate values.
